description:
This dataset contains the vocabulary of the ERA knowledge graph. The vocabulary of the ERA knowledge graph consists out of two different sources.

Sources:
- [The ontology](https://git.fpfis.eu/datateam/ERA/era-vocabulary/-/blob/master/ontology.ttl).Vocabulary defined by the European Union Agency for Railways to describe the concepts and relationships related to the European railway infrastructure and the vehicles authorized to operate over it. The file is synchronized on 2022-02-02.
- [The skos Concepts](https://git.fpfis.eu/datateam/ERA/era-vocabulary/-/raw/master/era-skos.ttl). Controlled SKOS-based vocabularies defined by the European Union Agency for Railways to describe concepts related to the European railway infrastructure and the vehicles authorized to operate over it. The file is synchronized on 2022-02-02.

ContactLineSystem.label: Contact Line System
ContactLineSystem.description: System that is used to transmit electrical energy to road or rail vehicles.

ETCSLevel.label: ETCS Level
ETCSLevel.description: ERTMS / ETCS application level related to the track side equipment.

LineReference.label: Line Reference
LineReference.description: A reference to a specific national railway line.

Manufacturer.label: Manufacturer
Manufacturer.description: A company or organization that manufactures vehicles.

NationalRailwayLine.label: National Railway Line
NationalRailwayLine.description: Railway line within a member state.

NetElement.label: Net Element
NetElement.description: Base class for defining nodes in the connectivity graph representing the topological network.

NetRelation.label: Net Relation
NetRelation.description: Base class for defining edges in the connectivity graph representing the topological network.

OperationalPoint.label: Operational Point
OperationalPoint.description: An operational point (OP) means any location for train service operations, where train services may begin and end or change route, and where passenger or freight services may be provided; operational point also means any location at boundaries between Member States or infrastructure managers.

Platform.label: Platform
Platform.description: Platform for the purpose of RINF is understood as a platform edge. A platform concerns only the part of the structure neighbouring to the track (interfaced with trains).

SectionOfLine.label: Section Of Line
SectionOfLine.description: A section of line means the part of line between adjacent operational points and may consist of several tracks.

Siding.label: Siding
Siding.description: Sidings are all those tracks where running trains in service movements ends and which are not used for operational routing of a train.

Signal.label: Signal
Signal.description: A railway signal is an installation next to the railway track for signalling the maximum allowed speed in the next block section to the train driver.

TSIMagneticFields.label: TSI mangnetic fields
TSIMagneticFields.description: Existence and TSI compliance of rules for magnetic fields emitted by a vehicle.

TSITractionHarmonics.label: TSI traction harmonics
TSITractionHarmonics.description: Existence and TSI compliance of limits in harmonics in the traction current of vehicles.

Track.label: Track
Track.description: A running track that is used for train service movements.

TrainDetectionSystem.label: Train Detection System
TrainDetectionSystem.description: System used to detect the position of vehicles in the railway track.

Tunnel.label: Tunnel
Tunnel.description: A railway tunnel is an excavation or a construction around the track provided to allow the railway to pass for example higher land, buildings or water.

Vehicle.label: Vehicle
Vehicle.description: A specific vehicle or wagon able to operate over railway lines.

VehicleKeeper.label: Vehicle Keeper
VehicleKeeper.description: A company or organization that owns or operates a certain vehicle.

VehicleType.label: Vehicle Type
VehicleType.description: A vehicle type that has been authorized to operate on the EU railway infrastructure.

accelerationLevelCrossing.label: acceleration allowed level crossings
accelerationLevelCrossing.description: Existence of limit for acceleration of train if stopping or recovering speed close to a level crossing expressed in a specific reference acceleration curve.

additionalBrakingInformationDocument.label: additional braking information document
additionalBrakingInformationDocument.description: Electronic document available in two EU languages from the IM stored by the Agency providing additional information as defined in point (2) of point 4.2.2.6.2 of the Annex to Regulation XXX - OPE TSI.

altitudeRangeDetail.label: altitude range detail
altitudeRangeDetail.description: Altitude range value for 'X' if value 'AX' is selected in altitude range.

areaBoardingAid.label: area boarding aid
areaBoardingAid.description: Information of the train access level for which the boarding aid can be used. Data is presented as the vertical difference that is overcome by the platform boarding aid in millimetres. The value “0” means that the platform is not equipped with a platform boarding aid.

assistanceStartingTrain.label: assistance starting train
assistanceStartingTrain.description: Indication of existence of equipment or staff supporting the train crew in starting the train.

authorizedCountry.label: authorized country
authorizedCountry.description: Indicates the country(ies) in where a vehicle type has been authorized to operate.

automaticDroppingDeviceRequired.label: automatic dropping device required
automaticDroppingDeviceRequired.description: Indication of whether an automatic dropping device (ADD) required on the vehicle.

axleSpacing.label: axle spacing
axleSpacing.description: Position of the axles along the unit. a: Distance between axles; b: Distance from end axle to the end of the nearest coupling plane; c: distance between two inside axles.

boardingAids.label: boarding aids
boardingAids.description: Description of any integrated boarding aids (if provided).

brakeWeightPercentage.label: brake weight percentage
brakeWeightPercentage.description: Brake weight percentage (lambda) or Braked mass.

cantDefficiency.label: cant defficiency
cantDefficiency.description: Cant deficiency (maximum uncompensated lateral acceleration) for which the vehicle has been assessed. For dual gauge vehicles values for each gauge have to be indicated.

cantDeficiency.label: cant deficiency
cantDeficiency.description: Maximum cant deficiency expressed in millimetres defined as difference between the applied cant and a higher equilibrium cant the line has been designed for.

catenaryMaxRatedCurrent.label: catenary max rated current
catenaryMaxRatedCurrent.description: Maximum rated current from the catenary (to be indicated for each electrical energy supply system the vehicle is equipped for), given in A.

compatibilityProcedureDocument.label: structure check document
compatibilityProcedureDocument.description: Document with the procedure(s) for static and dynamic route compatibility checks.

complianceInfTsi.label: compliance with INF TSI
complianceInfTsi.description: Compliance of the tunnel with INF TSI at the maximum permitted speed.

compositeBrakeBlockRetrofitted.label: composite brake block retrofitted
compositeBrakeBlockRetrofitted.description: Indicates if a vehicle's composite brake block is retrofitted

concepts/.description: Controlled SKOS-based vocabularies defined by the European Union Agency for Railways to describe concepts related to the European railway infrastructure and the vehicles authorized to operate over it.

contactLineSystemType.description: Indication of the type of the contact line system

contactStripMaterial.label: contact strip material
contactStripMaterial.description: Indication of which contact strip materials are permitted to be used.

crossSectionArea.label: cross section area
crossSectionArea.description: Smallest cross section area in square metres of the tunnel.

currentLimitationRequired.description: Indication of whether an on board current or power limitation function on vehicles is required.

dangerousGoodsTankCode.description: Dangerous goods for which the vehicle is suitable (tank code).

demonstrationSRT.description: Unique number for EI declarations concerning requirements of SRT (Safety in Railway Tunnels) TSI for infrastructure system.

dieselThermalAllowed.label: diesel thermal allowed
dieselThermalAllowed.description: Indication whether it is allowed to use diesel or other thermal traction in the tunnel.

distSignToPhaseEnd.label: distance sign and phase
distSignToPhaseEnd.description: Distance between the signboard authorizing the driver to “raise pantograph” or “close the circuit breaker” after passing the phase separation and the end of the phase separation section. Specific for route compatibility check on French network.

drivingCabs.label: driving cabs
drivingCabs.description: Number of driving cabs. For wagons the number of driving cabs is to be set to zero (0).

eddyCurrentBrakePrevention.label: eddy current brake prevention
eddyCurrentBrakePrevention.description: Possibility of preventing the use of the eddy current track brake (only if fitted with eddy current brake)

eddyCurrentBrakingConditionsDocument.label: eddy current braking conditions document
eddyCurrentBrakingConditionsDocument.description: Document with the conditions for the use of eddy current brakes.

elementA.label: element A
elementA.description: References the first topological object in an oriented relation.

elementB.label: element B
elementB.description: References the second topological object in an oriented relation.

elementPart.label: element part
elementPart.description: References the topology object of a higher-granularity level which contains a lower-granularity topology object.

emergencyBrake.label: emergency braking
emergencyBrake.description: Stopping distance and deceleration profile for each load condition per design maximum speed.

endCouplingType.label: end coupling type
endCouplingType.description: Type of end coupling (indicating tensile and compressive forces).

endIntrinsicCoordinate.label: end intrinsic coordinate
endIntrinsicCoordinate.description: Indicates the coordinate point where a linear object ends.

endLocation.label: end location
endLocation.description: References the geolocation of the end of a tunnel.

energyMeterInstalled.label: energy meter installed
energyMeterInstalled.description: TSI conform energy meter for billing purposes installed on board.

energySupplyMaxPower.label: energy supply max power
energySupplyMaxPower.description: Maximum power (to be indicated for each energy supply system the vehicle is equipped for), given in kW.

energySupplySystem.label: energy supply system
energySupplySystem.description: Indication of the traction supply system (nominal voltage and frequency).

energySupplySystemTSICompliant.label: energy supply system TSI compliant
energySupplySystemTSICompliant.description: Indication if the traction supply system (nominal voltage and frequency) is fully compliant with TSI.

eratvIndex.label: eratv index
eratvIndex.description: Index code used in the original definition of a parameter in ERATV.

etcsDataCommApp.label: ETCS data communication application
etcsDataCommApp.description: Data communication application for ETCS implementation.

etcsDegradedSituation.label: ETCS level for degraded situation
etcsDegradedSituation.description: ERTMS / ETCS application level for degraded situation related to the track side equipment.

etcsEquipmentOnBoardLevel.label: ETCS equipment level
etcsEquipmentOnBoardLevel.description: ETCS equipment on-board and its level.

etcsInfill.label: ETCS infill
etcsInfill.description: Information about installed trackside/on-board equipment capable to transmit infill information by loop or GSM-R for level 1 installation.

etcsInfillLineAccess.label: ETCS infill line access
etcsInfillLineAccess.description: Indication whether infill is required to access the line for safety reasons.

etcsLevel.label: etcs level
etcsLevel.description: ETCS level available in the section of line.

etcsLevelType.label: etcs level type
etcsLevelType.description: ERTMS / ETCS application level which expresses the possible operating relationships between track and train

etcsNationalApplications.label: ETCS national applications
etcsNationalApplications.description: ETCS national applications implemented (NID_XUSER of Packet 44).

etcsNationalPacket44.label: ETCS national packet 44
etcsNationalPacket44.description: Indication whether data for national packet 44 applications is transmitted between track and train.

etcsOptionalFunctions.label: ETCS optional functions
etcsOptionalFunctions.description: Optional ETCS functions which might improve operation on the line.

etcsSystemCompatibility.label: ETCS system compatibility
etcsSystemCompatibility.description: ETCS requirements used for demonstrating technical compatibility.

flangeLubeForbidden.label: flange lube forbidden
flangeLubeForbidden.description: Indication whether the use of on-board device for flange lubrication is forbidden

flangeLubeRules.label: flange lube rules
flangeLubeRules.description: Indication whether rules for activation or deactivation of flange lubrication exist.

flangeLubricationFitted.label: flange lubrication fitted
flangeLubricationFitted.description: Indicates if the vehicle type is fitted for flange lubrication.

freightCorridor.label: freight corridor
freightCorridor.description: Railway Freight Corridor that the line is designated to.

frenchTrainDetectionSystemLimitation.label: french train detection system limitation
frenchTrainDetectionSystemLimitation.description: Section with train detection limitation, specific for route compatibility check on French network.

gaugingCheckLocation.label: gauging check location
gaugingCheckLocation.description: Location of particular points requiring specific checks due to deviations from gauging. The location (generally the distance from the origin of the line to the centre) on a line is given in kilometres with decimals (precision of 0.001).

gaugingProfile.label: gauging profile
gaugingProfile.description: Gauges as defined in European standard or other local gauges, including lower or upper part.

gaugingTransversalDocument.label: gauging traversal document
gaugingTransversalDocument.description: Document with the transversal section of the particular points requiring specific checks.

gprsForETCS.label: GPRS for ETCS
gprsForETCS.description: Indication if GPRS can be used for ETCS.

gprsImplementationArea.label: GPRS implementation area
gprsImplementationArea.description: Indication of the area in which GPRS can be used for ETCS.

gradient.label: gradient
gradient.description: Maximum value of the gradient for stabling tracks expressed in millimetres per metre.

gradientProfile.label: gradient profile
gradientProfile.description: Sequence of gradient values and locations of change in gradient.

gsmRActiveMobiles.label: GSM-R active mobiles
gsmRActiveMobiles.description: Number of active GSM-R mobiles (EDOR) or simultaneous communication session on-board for ETCS Level 2 (or level 3) needed to perform radio block centre handovers without having an operational disruption.

gsmRAdditionalInfo.label: GSM-R additional network info
gsmRAdditionalInfo.description: Any additional information on network characteristics or corresponding document available from the IM and stored by the Agency, e.g.; interference level, leading to the recommendation of additional on-board protection.

gsmRNoCoverage.label: GSM-R no coverage
gsmRNoCoverage.description: Indication if there is no GSMR coverage.

gsmROptionalFunctions.label: GSM-R optional functions
gsmROptionalFunctions.description: Use of optional GSM-R functions which might improve operation on the line. They are for information only and not for network access criteria.

gsmRRadioDataCommunication.label: GSM-R radio data communication
gsmRRadioDataCommunication.description: GSM-R Radio Data communication on board and its Baseline.

gsmRSetsInDrivingCab.label: GSM-R sets in driving cab
gsmRSetsInDrivingCab.description: Number of GSM-R mobile sets in driving cab for data transmission.

gsmrNetworkCoverage.label: GSM-R network coverage
gsmrNetworkCoverage.description: GSM-R networks covered by a roaming agreement

hasAbstraction.label: has abstraction
hasAbstraction.description: Property that links a physical entity with its topological abstraction representation.

hasAdditionalBrakingInformation.label: has additional braking information
hasAdditionalBrakingInformation.description: Availability by the IM of additional information as defined in 4.2.2.6.2 (2) Regulation XXX - OPE TSI.

hasAutomaticDroppingDevice.label: has automatic dropping device
hasAutomaticDroppingDevice.description: Automatic dropping device (ADD) fitted (to be indicated for each energy supply system the vehicle is equipped for).

hasBallast.label: has ballast
hasBallast.description: Specifies whether track construction is with sleepers embedded in ballast or not..

hasCantDefficiencyCompensation.label: has cant defficiency compensation
hasCantDefficiencyCompensation.description: Vehicle equipped with a cant deficiency compensation system (tilting vehicle).

hasCurrentLimitation.label: has current limitation
hasCurrentLimitation.description: Electric units equipped with power or current limitation function.

hasETCSRestrictionsConditions.label: has ETCS restrictions conditions
hasETCSRestrictionsConditions.description: Indication whether restrictions or conditions due to partial compliance with the CCS TSI exist.

hasElectricShoreSupply.label: has electric shore supply
hasElectricShoreSupply.description: Indication whether an installation for electric shore supply exists (fixed installation for servicing trains).

hasExternalCleaning.label: has external cleaning
hasExternalCleaning.description: Indication whether exists an installation for external cleaning facility (fixed installation for servicing trains) as defined in INF TSIs.

hasHotAxleBoxDetector.label: has axle box detector
hasHotAxleBoxDetector.description: Existence of trackside hot axle box detector (HABD).

hasImplementation.label: has implementation
hasImplementation.description: Property that links a topological abstraction entity with its physical representation.

hasLevelCrossings.label: has level crossings
hasLevelCrossings.description: Indication whether level crossings (including pedestrian track crossing) exist on the section of line.

hasLubricationDevicePrevention.label: has lubrication device prevention
hasLubricationDevicePrevention.description: Possibility of preventing the use of the lubrication device (only if fitted with flange lubrication).

hasOtherTrainProtection.label: has other train protection
hasOtherTrainProtection.description: Indication if other train protection, control and warning systems in normal operation are installed lineside.

hasParkingBrake.label: has parking brake
hasParkingBrake.description: Indicates if a vehicle type has parking brake.

hasRefuelling.label: has refuelling
hasRefuelling.description: Indication whether exists an installation for refuelling (fixed installation for servicing trains) as defined in INF TSIs.

hasRegenerativeBrake.label: has regenerative brake
hasRegenerativeBrake.description: Indication whether regenerative braking is permitted or not.

hasSandRestocking.label: has sand restocking
hasSandRestocking.description: Indication whether an installation for sand restocking exists (fixed installation for servicing trains).

hasSandingPrevention.label: has sanding prevention
hasSandingPrevention.description: Possibility of preventing the use of sanding.

hasSevereWeatherConditions.label: has severe weather conditions
hasSevereWeatherConditions.description: Climatic conditions on the line are severe according to European standard.

hasShuntingRestrictions.label: has shunting restrictions
hasShuntingRestrictions.description: Indicates the presence of shunting restrictions.

hasSignal.label: has signal
hasSignal.description: References a signal associated with a topology object.

hasSystemSeparation.label: has system separation
hasSystemSeparation.description: Indication of existence of system separation.

hasTSITrainDetection.label: has TSI train detection
hasTSITrainDetection.description: Indication if there is any train detection system installed and fully compliant with the CCS TSI requirements.

hasToiletDischarge.label: has toilet discharge
hasToiletDischarge.description: Indication whether exists an installation for toilet discharge (fixed installation for servicing trains) as defined in INF TSIs.

hasTrainIntegrityConfirmation.label: has train integrity confirmation
hasTrainIntegrityConfirmation.description: Indication of on-board management system about completeness of the train information.

hasWaterRestocking.label: has water restocking
hasWaterRestocking.description: Indication whether exists an installation for water restocking (fixed installation for servicing trains) as defined in INF TSIs.

hasWheelSlideProtectionSystem.label: has wheel slide protection system
hasWheelSlideProtectionSystem.description: Indicates the presence of a wheel slide protection system.

highSpeedLoadModelCompliance.label: high speed load model compliance
highSpeedLoadModelCompliance.description: Compliance of structures with the High Speed Load Model (HSLM).

hotAxleBoxDetectorDirection.label: hot axle box detector direction
hotAxleBoxDetectorDirection.description: Direction of measurement of trackside HABD. Specific for the French Italian and Swedish networks.

hotAxleBoxDetectorGeneration.label: hot axle box detector generation
hotAxleBoxDetectorGeneration.description: Generation of trackside HABD. Specific for the French Italian and Swedish networks.

hotAxleBoxDetectorIdentification.label: hot axle box detector identification
hotAxleBoxDetectorIdentification.description: Identification of trackside HABD. Applicable if trackside HABD is not TSI compliant.

hotAxleBoxDetectorLocation.label: hot axle box detector location
hotAxleBoxDetectorLocation.description: Railway location of trackside HABD. Applicable if trackside HABD is not TSI compliant.

hotAxleBoxDetectorTSICompliant.label: hot axle box detector TSI compliant
hotAxleBoxDetectorTSICompliant.description: Trackside HABD TSI compliant. Specific for the French, Italian and Swedish networks.

inCountry.label: in country
inCountry.description: Indicates the country in which an entity resides.

isQuietRoute.label: is quiet route
isQuietRoute.description: Indication of a track being part of a route with noise restrictions

isSwitchable.label: is switchable
isSwitchable.description: Indicates if a signal can be switched to show different messages or if it is a static panel.

kilometer.label: kilometer
kilometer.description: Distance measured in kilometers from the origin of a national railway line.

legacyRadioSystem.label: legacy radio system
legacyRadioSystem.description: Indication of radio legacy systems installed

lineCategory.label: line category
lineCategory.description: Classification of a line according to the INF TSI.

lineReference.label: line referece
lineReference.description: Indicates a relationship with a national railway line at a specific kilometer point.

linearCoordinate.label: linear coordinate
linearCoordinate.description: Indicates the position of an object within a linear positioning system. For example, relative to a national railway line.

loadCapability.label: load capability
loadCapability.description: A combination of the line category and speed at the weakest point of the track.

loadingPlatformHeight.label: loadng platform height
loadingPlatformHeight.description: Height of loading platform (for flat wagons and combined transport), given in mm.

localRulesOrRestrictions.label: local rules or restrictions
localRulesOrRestrictions.description: Existence of rules and restrictions of a strictly local nature.

localRulesOrRestrictionsDoc.label: local rules or restrictions document
localRulesOrRestrictionsDoc.description: Documents regarding the rules or restrictions of a strictly local nature available by the IM.

magneticBrakePrevention.label: magnetic brake prevention
magneticBrakePrevention.description: Possibility of preventing the use of the magnetic track brake (only if fitted with magnetic brake)

magneticBrakingConditionsDocument.label: magnetic braking conditions document
magneticBrakingConditionsDocument.description: Document with the conditions for the use of magnetic brakes.

manufacturingCountry.label: manufacturing country
manufacturingCountry.description: Indicates the country in which a vehicle or vehicle type is manufactured.

massPerWheel.label: mass per wheel
massPerWheel.description: Mass per wheel, given in kg.

maxCurrentStandstillPantograph.label: maximum standstill current per pantograph
maxCurrentStandstillPantograph.description: Indication of the maximum allowable train current at standstill for DC systems expressed in amperes.

maxDistConsecutiveAxles.label: max distance consecutive axles
maxDistConsecutiveAxles.description: Indication of maximum permitted distance between two consecutive axles in case of TSI non-compliance, given in millimetres.

maxDistEndTrainFirstAxle.label: max distance end train first axles
maxDistEndTrainFirstAxle.description: Indication of maximum distance between end of train and first axle, given in millimetres, applicable for both sides (front and rear) of a vehicle or train.

maxFlangeHeight.label: max flange height
maxFlangeHeight.description: Maximum permitted flange height, given in millimiters.

maxImpedanceWheelset.label: max impedance wheelset
maxImpedanceWheelset.description: The value of maximum permitted impedance given in ohm in case of TSI non-compliance.

maxLengthVehicleNose.label: maximum length vehicle nose
maxLengthVehicleNose.description: Maximum length of the vehicle nose.

maxSandingOutput.label: max sanding output
maxSandingOutput.description: Maximum amount of sand accepted on the track within value of sanding output for 30s, given in grams.

maxTrainCurrent.label: maximum train current
maxTrainCurrent.description: Maximum current taken by the complete train (composition of one or more units) expressed in amperes.

maximumAltitude.label: maximum altitude
maximumAltitude.description: Highest point of the section of line above sea level in reference to Normal Amsterdam’s Peil (NAP). The value of the parameter shall be given in metres, with tolerance of +/-100m.

maximumAverageDeceleration.label: maximum average deceleration
maximumAverageDeceleration.description: Maximum train deceleration given in m/s².

maximumBrakeThermalEnergyCapacity.label: maximum brake thermal energy capacity
maximumBrakeThermalEnergyCapacity.description: Maximum brake thermal energy capacity given in kJ

maximumBrakingDistance.label: maximum braking distance
maximumBrakingDistance.description: The maximum value of the braking distance [in meters] of a train shall be given for the maximum line speed.

maximumContactWireHeight.label: maximum contact wire height
maximumContactWireHeight.description: Indication of the maximum contact wire height expressed in metres.

maximumLocomotivesCoupled.label: maximum locomotives coupled
maximumLocomotivesCoupled.description: Maximum number of trainsets or locomotives coupled together in multiple operation.

maximumPermittedSpeed.label: maximum permitted speed
maximumPermittedSpeed.description: Nominal maximum operational speed on the line as a result of INF, ENE and CCS subsystem characteristics expressed in kilometres/hour.

maximumServiceBrake.label: maximum service break
maximumServiceBrake.description: At maximum service brake: Stopping distance, Maximum deceleration, for the load condition 'design mass under normal payload' at the design maximum speed.

maximumSpeedAndCantDeficiency.label: maximum speed and cant deficiency
maximumSpeedAndCantDeficiency.description: Combination of maximum speed and maximum cant deficiency for which the vehicle was assessed.

maximumTemperature.label: maximum temperature
maximumTemperature.description: Maximum tempertaure allowed for unrestricted operation access, according to European standard.

maximumTrainDeceleration.label: maximum train deceleration
maximumTrainDeceleration.description: Limit for longitudinal track resistance given as a maximum allowed train deceleration and expressed in metres per square second.

meetsRequirementVehicleAuthorisation.label: meets requirement vehicle authorization
meetsRequirementVehicleAuthorisation.description: Type meets the requirements necessary for validity of the vehicle authorisation granted by one Member State in other MSs.

minAxleLoad.label: min axle load
minAxleLoad.description: Minimum permitted axle load, given in tons.

minAxleLoadVehicleCategory.label: min axle load per vehicle category
minAxleLoadVehicleCategory.description: Minimum permitted axle load per category of Vehicle, given in tons depending of the category of vehicle.

minDistConsecutiveAxles.label: min distance consecutive axles
minDistConsecutiveAxles.description: Indication of minimum permitted distance between two consecutive axles, given in millimetres.

minDistFirstLastAxle.label: min distance first and last axles
minDistFirstLastAxle.description: Indication of minimum permitted distance between first and last axles, given in millimetres.

minFlangeHeight.label: min flange height
minFlangeHeight.description: Minimum permitted flange height, given in millimiters.

minFlangeThickness.label: min flange thickness
minFlangeThickness.description: Minimum permitted flange thickness, given in millimiters.

minRimWidth.label: min rim width
minRimWidth.description: Minimum permitted width of the rim, given in millimiters.

minVehicleImpedance.label: minimum vehicle impedance
minVehicleImpedance.description: Minimum vehicle impedance (between wheels and pantograph) (only for vehicles equipped for 1500V or 3000V DC).

minWheelDiameter.label: min wheel diameter
minWheelDiameter.description: Minimum permitted wheel diameter, given in millimiters.

minimumConcaveVerticalRadius.label: minimum concave vertical radius
minimumConcaveVerticalRadius.description: Minimum vertical concave curve radius capability.

minimumContactWireHeight.label: minimum contact wire height
minimumContactWireHeight.description: Indication of the minimum contact wire height expressed in metres.

minimumConvexVerticalRadius.label: minimum convex vertical radius
minimumConvexVerticalRadius.description: Minimum vertical convex curve radius capability.

minimumHorizontalRadius.label: minimum horizontal radius
minimumHorizontalRadius.description: Radius of the smallest horizontal curve of the track in metres.

minimumTemperature.label: minimum temperature
minimumTemperature.description: Minimum tempertaure allowed for unrestricted operation access, according to European standard.

minimumVerticalRadius.label: minimum vertical curve radius
minimumVerticalRadius.description: Radius of the smallest vertical curve expressed in metres.

minimumWheelDiameter.label: minimum wheel diameter
minimumWheelDiameter.description: Maximum unguided length of fixed obtuse crossings is based on a minimum wheel diameter in service expressed in millimetres.

multipleTrainProtectionRequired.label: multiple train protection required
multipleTrainProtectionRequired.description: Indication whether more than one train protection, control and warning system is required to be on-board and active simultaneously.

nationalRollingStockFireCategory.label: national rolling stock fire category
nationalRollingStockFireCategory.description: Applicable national rolling stock fire category for a tunnel.

navigability.label: navigability
navigability.description: Indicates the navigation possibilities between two related topological objects.

notApplicable.label: not applicable
notApplicable.description: Reference to a property that is not applicable.

notYetAvailable.label: not yet available
notYetAvailable.description: Reference to a property that is not yet available.

numberElementsRakeFreightWagons.label: number elements rake freight wagons
numberElementsRakeFreightWagons.description: Number of elements in the rake of freight wagons (only for subcategory 'rake of freight wagons')

numberOfPantographsInContactWithOCL.label: number of pantographs in contact with OCL
numberOfPantographsInContactWithOCL.description: Number of pantographs in contact with the overhead contact line (OCL) (to be indicated for each energy supply system the vehicle is equipped for).

opEnd.label: OP end
opEnd.description: Operational Point at the end of a Section of Line.

opStart.label: OP start
opStart.description: Operational Point at the start of a Section of Line.

opType.label: operational point type
opType.description: Indicates the type on an operational point.

opTypeGaugeChangeover.label: track gauge changeover facility type
opTypeGaugeChangeover.description: Type of track gauge changeover facility.

operationalRestriction.label: operational restriction
operationalRestriction.description: Indicates an operational restriction of vehicle or wagon.

otherTrainProtection.label: other train protection
otherTrainProtection.description: Other train protection, control and warning systems for degraded situation.

pantographHead.label: tsi pantograph head
pantographHead.description: Indication of which TSI compliant pantograph heads are allowed to be used.

parkingBrakeMandatory.label: parking brake mandatory
parkingBrakeMandatory.description: All vehicles of this type must be equipped with a parking brake (parking brake mandatory for vehicles of this type).

parkingBrakeMaximumGradient.label: parking brake maximum gradient
parkingBrakeMaximumGradient.description: Maximum gradient on which the unit is kept immobilised by the parking brake alone (if the vehicle is fitted with it).

parkingBrakeType.label: parking brake type
parkingBrakeType.description: Parking brake type (if the vehicle is fitted with it).

passByNoiseLevel.label: pass-by noise level
passByNoiseLevel.description: Pass-by noise level given in dB(A).

passesThroughTunnel.label: passes through tunnel
passesThroughTunnel.description: References a tunnel that a track goes through.

permissiblePayload.label: permissible payload
permissiblePayload.description: Permissible payload for different line categories.

permittedContactForce.label: permitted contact force
permittedContactForce.description: Indication of contact force allowed expressed in newtons.

phaseSeparation.label: phase separation
phaseSeparation.description: Indication of existence of phase separation and required information.

platformHeight.label: platform height
platformHeight.description: Distance between the upper surface of platform and running surface of the neighbouring track. It is the nominal value expressed in millimetres.

platformId.label: platform id
platformId.description: Unique platform identification or number within an Operational Point.

portableBoardingAids.label: portable boarding aids
portableBoardingAids.description: Description of any portable boarding aids if considered in the design of the vehicle for meeting the PRM TSI requirements.

positionOnA.label: position on A
positionOnA.description: Determines the position of the topological object A in a relation.

positionOnB.label: position on B
positionOnB.description: Determines the position of the topological object B in a relation.

preventRegenerativeBrakeUse.label: prevent regenerative brake use
preventRegenerativeBrakeUse.description: Possibility of preventing the use of the regenerative brake (only if fitted with regenerative brake).

profileNumberSemiTrailers.label: profile number for semi-trailers
profileNumberSemiTrailers.description: Coding for combined transport for semi-trailers as defined in UIC Code.

profileNumberSwapBodies.label: profile number for swap bodies
profileNumberSwapBodies.description: Coding for combined transport with swap bodies as defined in UIC Code.

protectionLegacySystem.label: protection legacy system
protectionLegacySystem.description: Indication of which class B system is installed

publicNetworkRoaming.label: public network roaming
publicNetworkRoaming.description: Existence of roaming to public networks.

publicNetworkRoamingDetails.label: public network roaming details
publicNetworkRoamingDetails.description: Details on roaming to public networks.

quasiStaticGuidingForce.label: quasi static guiding force
quasiStaticGuidingForce.description: Quasi-static guiding force (if exceeds the limit defined in TSI or not defined in the TSI), given in kN.

quieterRoutesExemptedCountry.label: quieter route exempted country
quieterRoutesExemptedCountry.description: Country where a vehicle may operate without noise restrictions

radioSwitchOverSpecialConditions.label: radio switch over special conditions
radioSwitchOverSpecialConditions.description: Special conditions implemented on-board to switch over between different radio systems. Given as combination of systems installed on board ('System XX'_'System YY').

railInclination.label: rail inclination
railInclination.description: An angle defining the inclination of the head of a rail relative to the running surface.

raisedPantographsDistanceAndSpeed.label: raised pantographs distance and speed
raisedPantographsDistanceAndSpeed.description: Indication of maximum number of raised pantographs per train allowed and minimum spacing centre line to centre line of adjacent pantograph heads, expressed in metres, at the given speed.

redLightsRequired.label: red lights required
redLightsRequired.description: Indication of a sections where two steady red lights are required in accordance with Regulation (EU) 2019/773

referencePassByNoiseLevel.label: reference pass-by noise level
referencePassByNoiseLevel.description: Pass-by noise level was measured under reference conditions.

relativePosition.label: relative position
relativePosition.description: Indicates the position of an object relative to the linear coordinates of the associated topological object.

requiredSandingOverride.label: required sanding override
requiredSandingOverride.description: Indication whether possibility to activate/deactivate sanding devices by driver, according to instructions from the Infrastructure Manager, is required or not.

rinfIndex.label: rinf index
rinfIndex.description: Index code used in the original definition of a parameter in RINF.

rollingStockFireCategory.label: rolling stock fire category
rollingStockFireCategory.description: Applicable rolling stock fire category for a tunnel.

shortestDistanceBetweenPantographsInCont.label: shortest distance between pantographs in contact with OCL
shortestDistanceBetweenPantographsInCont.description: Shortest distance between two pantographs in contact with the OCL (to be indicated for each energy supply system the vehicle is equipped for; to be indicated for single and, if applicable, multiple operation) (only if number of raised pantographs is more than 1).

sidingId.label: siding id
sidingId.description: Unique siding identification or number within an Operational Point.

solNature.label: section of line nature
solNature.description: Indicates the nature of a section of line.

specificInformation.label: specific information
specificInformation.description: This parameters allows the IM to provide plain text with specific information about the track.

startIntrinsicCoordinate.label: start intrinsic coordinate
startIntrinsicCoordinate.description: Indicates the coordinate point where a linear object begins.

startLocation.label: start location
startLocation.description: References the geolocation of the start of a tunnel.

startingNoiseLevel.label: starting noise level
startingNoiseLevel.description: starting noise level given in dB(A).

staticAxleLoadExceptionalPayload.label: static axle load under exceptional payload
staticAxleLoadExceptionalPayload.description: Static axle load under exceptional payload.

staticAxleLoadNormalPayload.label: static axle load under normal payload
staticAxleLoadNormalPayload.description: Static axle load under normal payload.

staticAxleLoadWorkingOrder.label: static axle load in working order
staticAxleLoadWorkingOrder.description: Static axle load in working order.

stationaryNoiseLevel.label: stationary noise level
stationaryNoiseLevel.description: stationary noise level given in dB(A).

structureCheckLocation.label: structure check location
structureCheckLocation.description: Railway location of structures requiring specific checks.

supportedPlatformHeight.label: supported platform height
supportedPlatformHeight.description: Platform height for which the vehicle is de­signed.

switchProtectControlWarning.label: switch protect control warning
switchProtectControlWarning.description: Existence of switch over between different protection, control and warning systems while running.

switchRadioSystem.label: switch radio system
switchRadioSystem.description: Indication whether a switch over between different radio systems and no communication system whilst running exist.

systemSeparationInfo.label: system separation information
systemSeparationInfo.description: Required information on system separation. Data is structured as: length [NNN] + switch off breaker [Y/N] + lower pantograph [Y/N] +[CharacterString].

tenGISId.label: TEN GIS identity
tenGISId.description: Indication of the GIS identity (GIS ID) of the section of TEN-T database to which the track belongs.

thermalCapacityDistance.label: thermal capacity distance
thermalCapacityDistance.description: Thermal capacity distance. If no reference case is indicated.

thermalCapacityGradient.label: thermal capacity gradient
thermalCapacityGradient.description: Thermal capacity gradient. If no reference case is indicated.

thermalCapacitySpeed.label: thermal capacity speed
thermalCapacitySpeed.description: Thermal capacity speed. If no reference case is indicated.

thermalCapacityTSIReference.label: thermal capacity TSI reference
thermalCapacityTSIReference.description: Reference case of a TSI thermal capacity.

thermalCapacityTime.label: thermal capacity time
thermalCapacityTime.description: Thermal capacity time. If no reference case is indicated.

tiltingSupported.label: tilting supported
tiltingSupported.description: Indication whether tilting functions are supported by ETCS.

totalVehicleMass.label: total vehicle mass
totalVehicleMass.description: Total vehicle mass (for each vehicle of the unit), given in kg.

track.label: track
track.description: Reference to a related railway track.

trackId.label: track id
trackId.description: Unique track identification or unique track number within a Section of Line.

trainControlSwitchOverSpecialConditions.label: train control switch over special conditions
trainControlSwitchOverSpecialConditions.description: Special conditions implemented on-board to switch over between different train protection control and warning systems. Given as combination of systems installed on board ('System XX'_'System YY').

trainDetectionSystem.label: train detection system
trainDetectionSystem.description: Train detection systems installed in the section of line.

trainDetectionSystemSpecificCheck.label: detection system specific check
trainDetectionSystemSpecificCheck.description: Type of track circuits or axle counter to which specific checks are needed.

trainDetectionSystemSpecificCheckDocumen.label: detection system specific check document
trainDetectionSystemSpecificCheckDocumen.description: Document with the procedure(s) related to the type of track circuits declared in 1.1.1.3.7.1.2.

trainDetectionSystemType.label: train detection system type
trainDetectionSystemType.description: Indication of supported types of train detection systems.

trainIntegrityOnBoardRequired.label: train integrity on-board required
trainIntegrityOnBoardRequired.description: Indication whether Train Integrity monitoring system (TIMS) is required to access the line for safety reasons.

transportableOnFerry.label: transportable on ferry
transportableOnFerry.description: Indicates the suitability for transport on ferries.

tsiCompliant.label: tsi compliant
tsiCompliant.description: Indicates if a certain property is TSI compliant.

tsiCompliantCompositeBrakeBlocks.label: TSI compliant composite brake blocks
tsiCompliantCompositeBrakeBlocks.description: TSI compliance of rules on the use of composite brake blocks.

tsiCompliantFerromagneticWheel.label: TSI compliant ferromagnetic wheel material
tsiCompliantFerromagneticWheel.description: TSI compliance of Ferromagnetic characteristics of wheel material required.

tsiCompliantMaxDistConsecutiveAxles.label: TSI compliant max distance consecutive axles
tsiCompliantMaxDistConsecutiveAxles.description: Indication whether required distance between two consecutive axles is compliant with the TSI.

tsiCompliantMaxImpedanceWheelset.label: TSI compliant max impedance wheelset
tsiCompliantMaxImpedanceWheelset.description: TSI compliance of maximum permitted impedance between opposite wheels of a wheelset.

tsiCompliantMetalConstruction.label: TSI compliant metal construction
tsiCompliantMetalConstruction.description: TSI compliance of rules for vehicle metal construction.

tsiCompliantMetalFreeSpace.label: TSI compliant metal free space
tsiCompliantMetalFreeSpace.description: TSI compliance of rules for metal-free space around wheels.

tsiCompliantRSTShuntImpedance.label: TSI compliant RST shunt impedance
tsiCompliantRSTShuntImpedance.description: TSI compliance of rules on combination of RST characteristics influencing shunting impedance.

tsiCompliantSandCharacteristics.label: TSI compliant sand characteristics
tsiCompliantSandCharacteristics.description: TSI Compliance of rules on sand characteristics.

tsiCompliantSanding.label: TSI compliant sanding
tsiCompliantSanding.description: TSI compliance of sanding rules to allow compatibility with track circuits. Too much sand brings the risk of not detecting trains in tracks equipped with track circuits.

tsiCompliantShuntDevices.label: TSI compliant shunt devices
tsiCompliantShuntDevices.description: TSI compliance of rules on shunt assisting devices.

tsiSwitchCrossing.label: TSI compliance for switches and crossings
tsiSwitchCrossing.description: Switches and crossings are maintained to in service limit dimension as specified in TSI.

tunnelDocRef.label: tunnel document reference
tunnelDocRef.description: Reference to a document available from the IM with precise description of the tunnel.

tunnelIdentification.label: tunnel identification
tunnelIdentification.description: Unique tunnel identification or unique number within Member State.

typeVersionNumber.label: type version number
typeVersionNumber.description: Serial number that identifies a vehicle type.

umax2.label: umax2
umax2.description: Umax2 for lines referred to in sections 7.4.2.2.1 and 7.4.2.11.1 of Regulation (EU)1301/2014. Specific for the French network.

uopid.label: unique operational point id
uopid.description: Code composed of country code and alphanumeric operational point code, as defined in RINF.

vehicleKeeper.label: vehicle keeper
vehicleKeeper.description: Indicates the organization that owns/operated a vehicle or wagon.

vehicleMaxSandingOutput.label: vehicle max sanding output
vehicleMaxSandingOutput.description: Vehicle Maximum sanding output, given in grams per second.

vehicleNumber.label: vehicle number
vehicleNumber.description: Identification number of a vehicle or wagon.

vehiclePantographHead.label: vehicle pantograph head
vehiclePantographHead.description: Pantograph head geometry (to be indicated for each energy supply system the vehicle is equipped for).

vehicleType.label: vehicle type
vehicleType.description: Indicates the vehicle type of a specific vehicle or wagon.

vehiclesComposingFixedFormation.label: vehicles composing fixed formation
vehiclesComposingFixedFormation.description: Number of vehicles composing the fixed formation (for fixed formation only). Note: the value is mandatory for all vehicle categories. If the vehicle is composed of only one car, the indicated value shall be '1'.

verificationCSS.label: declaration of verification CSS
verificationCSS.description: Unique number for EC declarations concerning requirements of CSS (Command - Control and Signalling subsystem) on the specific track.

verificationENE.label: declaration of verification ENE
verificationENE.description: Unique number for EC declarations concerning requirements of ENE (ENErgy subsystem) on the specific track.

verificationINF.label: declaration of verification INF
verificationINF.description: Unique number for EC declarations concerning requirements of INF (INFrastructure) TSI.

verificationSRT.label: declaration of verification SRT
verificationSRT.description: Unique number for EC declarations concerning requirements of SRT (Safety in Railway Tunnels) TSI for infrastructure system.

voiceGSMRNetwork.label: voice GSM-R network
voiceGSMRNetwork.description: Voice SIM Card GSM-R Home Network

voiceRadioCompatible.label: voice radio compatible
voiceRadioCompatible.description: Radio requirements used for demonstrating technical compatibility voice

wheelSetGauge.label: wheel set gauge
wheelSetGauge.description: A single value expressed in millimetres that identifies the track and vehicle wheel set gauge.

wheelSetGaugeTransformationMethod.label: wheel set gauge transformation method
wheelSetGaugeTransformationMethod.description: Wheel gauge transformation method. Defined if more than one wheel gauges have been selected.

wheelchairSleepingPlaces.label: wheelchair sleeping spaces
wheelchairSleepingPlaces.description: Number of wheelchair accessible sleeping places.
